properties.description: Squamish habitat: forest edge Squamish location: Smoke Bluffs Park flowering
iNaturalist
well established in a crack on a S facing granitic cliff

Small tree (4 metres approx); top half of the leaves are toothed; flowers are white, showy, in erect clusters of up to 15 blooms. Location is edge of forest at top of slope leading down to Mashiter Creek. Second photo shows buds on adjacent branch.
Looks a bit like Ninebark but too far inland for it.
So far I am unsure what species is causing the galls. See the photos with the fluffy white later stage in case this helps with i.d.
